.TH "ovs_vport_alloc" 9 "ovs_vport_alloc" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ovs_vport_alloc \- allocate and initialize new vport
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct vport *" ovs_vport_alloc
.BI "(int priv_size "  ","
.BI "const struct vport_ops *ops "  ","
.BI "const struct vport_parms *parms "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "priv_size" 12
Size of private data area to allocate.
.IP "ops" 12
vport device ops
.IP "parms" 12
information about new vport.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Allocate and initialize a new vport defined by \fIops\fP.  The vport will contain
a private data area of size \fIpriv_size\fP that can be accessed using
\fBvport_priv\fP.  Some parameters of the vport will be initialized from \fIparms\fP.
\fIvports\fP that are no longer needed should be released with
\fBvport_free\fP.
